==History==
Skotizo was a general of [[Zamorak]] during the [[God Wars]], but he was often outshined by Zamorak's more notable generals, such as [[Thammaron]] and [[K'ril Tsutsaroth]]. He is also [[Zalcano]]'s brother.

After the cunning he and his soldiers showed at the Battle of [[Carrallanger]], Zamorak personally gave them their next mission, something he rarely did. The mission was to lead an expedition to recover a certain artefact in the [[Karamjan Temple]] found within the [[Kharazi Jungle]]. Skotizo was delighted by being assigned the mission and set out as soon as possible to please his god.

Reaching the Temple after a few days, Skotizo and his squad had managed to reach the Temple's centre after navigating a large maze. Now in possession of the artefact, Skotizo betrayed his squad, taking the artefact's power for himself and decimating the expedition team. This resulted in a furious Zamorak placing responsibility on Zalcano, inflicting a curse that would slowly turn her into stone until she could bring him before her god to face retribution.

Skotizo managed to avoid Zamorak's wrath during this time and discovered [[Great Kourend]] to the far west, while his sister believed that he had fled to the lands of [[Tirannwn]]. Using the power of the artefact, Skotizo managed to call a large amount of creatures to his side and set up in Kourend's underground, now the present-day [[Catacombs of Kourend]]. His arrival was noted by the [[Dragonkin]] [[Karuulm]], though he had opted to avoid confrontation and left Skotizo alone, who was likely unaware of his presence. Roughly 200 years after the end of a civil war in Kourend, Skotizo encountered a human adventurer in his chamber who was investigating mysterious disappearances and mortally wounded them.{{CiteText|text=Bloody diary|author=Unknown|quote=I placed the key and was teleported into a large, empty chamber. I thought myself alone, until a large, dark demon made its presence known to me. I stabbed it with my sword, but it seemed to have no effect. Did the shards weaken it after all? Or was it too powerful for the sword to harm it? Before I could gather my thoughts, the demon grabbed me and threw me across the chamber, breaking my spine. Before it could reach me, I spotted a portal in the corner of the room. I did not care where it led me, as long as it was far away from that demon. I ended up right here, by the altar where I had placed that key. I continue to write in my diary, hoping someone would come to rescue me.}}

